-- Bosch May Make Acquisitions in Brazil, to Invest There in 2010, Valor Says
-- Laura Price
-- 2010-06-25T11:23:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/bosch-may-make-acquisitions-in-brazil-to-invest-there-in-2010-valor-says.html

          
          
             Robert Bosch GmbH  may make
acquisitions in Brazil and plans to invest 45 million reais ($25
million) this year in fixed assets in the South American
country, Valor Economico reported, citing  Andreas Nobis , head of
the Latin American unit.  
 Bosch invested more than 1 billion reais in the last seven
years in Brazil, the Sao Paulo-based newspaper said. The company
may also seek business opportunities in Chile and Colombia,
Nobis told the newspaper. He declined to give details on any
possible acquisitions, Valor said.  
